Test for #28234:

Complexity: 3

- [x] any platform - @roblourens
- [x] Mac OS - @sandy081 

We now have minimal "proposed" extension API for VS Code debugging.

The first two pieces to verify are the `createDebugSession` request for launching a debug session based on a launch config passed as an argument and the `onDidTerminateDebugSession` event which indicates that a debug session has terminated.
See https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/issues/28234#issuecomment-310486799 for details and how to use the proposed API.

to verify:
- create "hello world" extension with yo
- register an "onDidTerminateDebugSession" handler in the `activate` function, e.g.:
  ```js
  context.subscriptions.push(vscode.debug.onDidTerminateDebugSession(s => { 
     console.log(`terminated: ${s.type} ${s.name}`);
  }));

- in the "extension.sayHello" command call "vscode.debug.createDebugSession", e.g.: 
  ```js
        vscode.debug.createDebugSession({
            type: 'node',
            name: 'foo bar',
            request: 'launch',
            program: '/Users/xxx/Projects/TestProjects/test.js'
        }).then(s => {
            console.log(`ok: ${s.type} ${s.name}`)
        }, err => {
            console.log(err)
        });
  ```
- run the extension and trigger the "Hello" command.
- verify that a debug session starts
- verify that termination of any debug sessions triggers an event with a DebugSession parameter that has the corresponding "type" and "name" attributes.
